The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) headquarters in which he expressed support for the agency and condemned calls for its abolition. Pence praised the work of ICE agents in enforcing immigration laws and protecting the American people. He highlighted the agency's efforts in arresting gang members, human traffickers, and drug cartels, as well as its role in preventing terrorism. Pence emphasized the importance of ICE's mission and the need for resources and support. He also criticized the attacks and threats against ICE officers and their families, calling for them to stop. Pence concluded by assuring ICE agents that they have the support and prayers of the American people and vowed that the Trump administration will continue to stand with them.